    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Write the a.c. current \( i={@na2a@}\cos({@na2c@}t)+ {@na2b@}\sin({@na2c@}t) \) in the form \( C\cos({@na2c@}t-\alpha) \).</p>
<p>Approximate all floating point numbers up to \(4\) d.p.</p>
<p>\(i = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We are given the a.c. current \( i={@na2a@}\cos({@na2c@}t)+ {@na2b@}\sin({@na2c@}t) .\)</p>
<p>We know that \(C= \sqrt{{@na2a@}^2+ {@na2b@}^2}\).</p>
<p>\( \tan\alpha=\dfrac{{@na2b@}}{{@na2a@}}\) and \(\alpha\) must be in the first quadrant (since \(A={@na2a@}, B={@na2b@} \) are <i>both positive.</i>)</p>
<p>Therefore \( \alpha=\tan^{-1}\dfrac{{@na2b@}}{{@na2a@}}={@ta2a@} \, \mathrm{rad}\), and then</p>
\[i={@ta2f@}.\]]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
